# ⚖️ Licensing: The Crosswalk Open Pledge

The "Not Just a Crosswalk" SAO is a work of open-source resistance. To ensure that visibility remains permanent and unerasable, this project is released under a "Strong Reciprocal" triple-license strategy.

### 1. Hardware (PCB & Schematics)
The hardware designs, including KiCad/EasyEDA files, schematics, and Gerber files, are licensed under the **CERN-OHL-S v2** (CERN Open Hardware Licence – Strongly Reciprocal). 
* Any modifications to the hardware must be shared under this same license.

### 2. Firmware (Source Code)
The firmware is licensed under the **GNU General Public License v3 (GPLv3)**. 
* This project incorporates the `CH32V003 WS2812 Driver` by Blake Sands, licensed under GPLv3. 
* All derivative firmware, including new animations or flags, must remain open-source under GPLv3.

### 3. Documentation & Creative Works
The silkscreen art, badge graphics, `README.md`, `CITATION.md`, and all marketing materials are licensed under **Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International (CC BY-SA 4.0)**.

